1
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:27,158
<i>Come to Los Angeles.</i>

2
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:29,232
<i>The sun shines bright.</i>

3
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:31,516
<i>The beaches are wide and inviting.</i>

4
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:35,435
<i>And the orange groves stretch
as far as the eye can see.</i>

5
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:39,357
<i>There are jobs aplenty. Land is cheap.</i>

6
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,750
<i>Every workingman
can have his own house.</i>

7
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:46,152
<i>And inside every house,
a happy all-American family.</i>

8
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,716
<i>You can have all this, and who knows?</i>

9
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:51,391
<i>You could even be discovered...</i>

10
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:54,758
<i>...become a movie star,
or at least see one.</i>

11
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:57,270
<i>Life is good in Los Angeles.</i>

12
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:00,160
<i>It's paradise on earth.</i>

13
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:03,911
<i>That's what they tell you, anyway.</i>

14
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:05,878
<i>Because they're selling an image.</i>

15
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:09,556
<i>They're selling it through
movies, radio and television.</i>

16
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:13,509
<i>In the hit show, Badge of Honor,
the L.A. Cops walk on water...</i>

17
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:15,512
<i>...as they keep the city clean
of crooks.</i>

18
00:01:17,040 --> 00:01:19,429
<i>You'd think this place
was the Garden of Eden.</i>

19
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,318
<i>But there's trouble in paradise...</i>

20
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,232
<i>...and his name is Meyer Harris Cohen,
Mickey C to his fans.</i>

21
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:29,029
<i>Local L.A. Color to the nth degree.</i>

22
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,391
<i>And his number one bodyguard...</i>

23
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:33,278
<i>...Johnny Stompanato.</i>

24
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:36,193
<i>Mickey C's the head of organized crime
in these parts.</i>

25
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:39,631
<i>He runs dope, rackets and prostitution.</i>

26
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,393
<i>He kills a dozen people a year.</i>

27
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,468
<i>And the dapper little gent
does it in style.</i>

28
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:47,674
<i>And every time his picture's
on the front page...</i>

29
00:01:48,160 --> 00:01:50,799
<i>...it's a black eye for the
image of Los Angeles.</i>

30
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:53,594
<i>Because how can organized crime exist...</i>

31
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:56,798
<i>...in the city with the best
police force in the world?</i>

32
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,519
<i>Something has to be done.</i>

33
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:01,633
<i>But nothing too original
because this is Hollywood.</i>

34
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,830
<i>What worked for Capone
would work for the Mickster.</i>

35
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:06,672
Mr. Cohen, you're under arrest.

36
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,115
Non-payment of federal income tax.

37
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:13,195
<i>But all is not well. Sending Mickey up
has created a vacuum.</i>

38
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:15,078
<i>And it's only a matter of time...</i>

39
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:18,790
<i>...before someone with balls
of brass tries to fill it.</i>

40
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:21,509
Remember, dear readers...

41
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:23,953
...you heard it here first...

42
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,558
...off the record...

43
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:28,872
...on the q. T...

44
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,839
...and very...

45
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,798
<i>...Hush-Hush.</i>

46
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,357
You're like Santa Claus with that list.

47
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,790
Except everyone on it's been naughty.

48
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,556
Guy's been out of Q two weeks.

49
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,635
Leave it for later.

50
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:03,838
We got to pick up the booze
and get it to the station.

51
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,918
Hollywood, this is 6-Adam-7.

52
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:11,915
Have Central send a prowler
to 4216 Evergreen.

53
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,833
Parole violation: Assault arising
from a family dispute.

54
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,672
We won't be here but
they'll see him.

55
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,069
Quit your whining!

56
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:29,436
Quit whining all the time!
It makes me sick!

57
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,749
Shut up!

58
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,588
Who the hell are you?

59
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,871
The ghost of Christmas past.

60
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:51,199
Dance with a man for a change?

61
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,919
You a smart ass?

62
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:10,032
You'll be out in a year and a half.
I'll get cozy with your parole officer.

63
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:14,159
Touch her again, I'll have you
violated on a kiddie-raper beef.

64
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,274
You know what they do
to kiddie rapers in Quentin.

65
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,872
You got someplace you can go?

66
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,952
Go get yourself fixed up.

67
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:37,835
Merry Christmas.

68
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,875
- Merry Christmas, ma'am.
- Let's go, Bud.

69
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,314
The guys are waiting.

70
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,631
<i>What do you do on Badge of Honor?</i>

71
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,394
I'm the technical advisor.

72
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:54,837
I teach Brett Chase how to
walk and talk like a cop.

73
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,510
Brett Chase doesn't walk
and talk like you.

74
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,876
That's because he's the
television version.

75
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:02,470
America isn't ready for the real me.

76
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:05,314
Is it true you arrested Bob Mitchum?

77
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:10,358
<i>The Badge of Honor guys like to pretend,
but the real thing must be a thrill.</i>

78
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:14,633
Why don't we go someplace quiet?
I'll give you the lowdown on Mitchum.

79
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:17,110
Big V. Jack Vincennes.

80
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,192
- May I have this dance?
- Of course.

81
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:21,431
<i>This is Sid Hudgens,
Hush-Hush magazine.</i>

82
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:24,114
- Hello, Karen.
- Hello yourself.

83
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,709
What that's about?

84
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:30,316
Her name was in a piece we did,
"Ingenue Dikes in Hollywood. "

85
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:35,028
My friend just sold reefer
to Matt Reynolds.

86
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:38,238
He's tripping the light fantastic
with Tammy Jordan.

87
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,517
Sorry, I lost you for a second.

88
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:45,958
Contract players, Metro. Pinch them,
I do you up a nice feature next issue.

89
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:48,555
- Plus your usual $50 cash.
- I need another $50.

90
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:51,957
Two 20s for two patrolmen,
a dime for the watch commander.

91
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,394
It's Christmas.

92
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:55,868
No, it's not.

93
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:58,156
It's felony possession of marijuana.

94
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:02,910
Actually, it's circulation 36,000
and climbing.

95
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,879
There's no telling where this will go.
Radio, television...

96
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:09,869
Once you whet the public's appetite
for the truth, the sky's the limit.

97
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:17,673
Sgt. Ed Exley, son of the
legendary Preston Exley.

98
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,473
Must be a hard act to follow.

99
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:24,077
Why not make a mark elsewhere?
Why become a cop?

100
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,232
I like to help people.

101
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,914
We heard 2 officers
were assaulted this evening.

102
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,799
- What do you think of that?
- Goes with the job.

103
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,797
Luckily, they're okay.

104
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,871
Aren't you young to be
watch commander?

105
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:36,996
It's only tonight.

106
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,914
The married men have Christmas Eve off.

107
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,957
That's a good lead for the story.

108
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,633
Merry Christmas, Captain.

109
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:46,628
- Captain Smith.
- Drop the formalities, Bobby.

110
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:50,315
- It's Christmas Eve, call me Dudley.
- I got the story's title.

111
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:53,193
I'm calling it
"Silent Night with the LAPD."

112
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,833
That's grand.

113
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,598
Remember that's "Smith"
with an "S."

114
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,237
Thank you, Merry Christmas.

115
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,709
Hold on, lads.

116
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,154
Merry Christmas.

117
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:14,434
I saw the results
on the lieutenant's exam.

118
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,318
First out of 23.

119
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:20,190
What'll it be, then? Patrol Division?
Internal Affairs? What?

120
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,998
Detective Bureau.

121
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,313
You're a political animal.

122
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:32,472
You have the eye for human weakness,
but not the stomach.

123
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:35,709
You're wrong, sir.

124
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:39,475
Would you be willing to plant evidence
on a suspect you knew to be guilty...

125
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,472
...to insure an indictment?

126
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,676
- We've been over this.
- Yes or no?

127
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:48,829
Would you beat a confession
out of a suspect you knew to be guilty?

128
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:51,879
Would you shoot a hardened
criminal in the back...

129
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:55,112
...in order to offset the chance
that some lawyer...

130
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,319
Then for the love of God...

131
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,198
...don't be a detective.

132
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:01,954
Stick to assignments where you don't
have to make those choices.

133
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:04,431
Dudley, I know you mean well...

134
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:08,235
...but I don't need to do it
the way you did... or my father.

135
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,437
At least get rid of the glasses.

136
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:14,240
I can't think of a man
in the Bureau who wears them.

137
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:25,071
If I ever get held up,
you better be here.

138
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,915
Hi, Nick.

139
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:33,513
I need a delivery.

140
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:36,228
A case each of gin, rum, Scotch.

141
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,829
Sounds like a hell of a party.
Be right with you.

142
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,075
Merry Christmas.

143
00:08:59,920 --> 00:09:01,717
Merry Christmas, Officer.

144
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:05,349
That obvious?

145
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:08,310
It's practically stamped
on your forehead.

146
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,355
There you go.

147
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,878
See what he wants, Buzz.

148
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,631
Get lost, why don't you?

149
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,716
Down!
Get your fucking head down.

150
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,678
I got a license for that.

151
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:08,434
Cut me some slack.
I used to be a cop.

152
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,591
"Leland Meeks"?
Never heard of you.

153
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,308
They call me Buzz.

154
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:16,551
I don't give a rat's ass.
Keep your head down.

155
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,518
And stay there... Buzz.

156
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,634
You okay?

157
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:23,990
She's fine.

158
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,714
I'm not asking you.

159
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:28,669
Who hit you?

160
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,797
It's not what you think.

161
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:35,075
What, then?

162
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:37,675
You got the wrong idea.
I'm fine.

163
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:41,190
But it's nice to know you care.

164
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,875
Drive safely.

165
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,755
What's going on?

166
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,635
You know him?

167
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:00,712
Yeah, I've seen him around.

168
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,999
He used to be a cop.

169
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:13,318
They're sitting in the dark,
goofing on the Christmas tree.

170
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,437
Put your camera right there.

171
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:19,798
When I walk out, get the
movie premiere in the background.

172
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:22,793
I like it, I like it.
"The Movie Premiere Pot Bust. "

173
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:25,873
I don't want those goddamn
floodlights of yours in my eyes.

174
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,588
Consider it done.
You hear that, Chip?

175
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:30,996
Come on. Get down.

176
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:35,636
Go! Pop them!

177
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,109
Freeze! Police!

178
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,115
Jesus Christ!

179
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:45,590
Come on.
Come on, let's go.

180
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,909
My family's coming...

181
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:50,277
- It'll be a nice Christmas gift.
- Hi, Tammy. Hi, Matt.

182
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:51,475
Over here.

183
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,597
- Just turn.
- Hold it. Got it!

184
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:58,513
- The Movie Premiere Pot Bust!
- Take them. I'll get the evidence.

185
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:12,715
"It's Christmas Eve
in the City of Angels.

186
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:15,952
And while decent citizens sleep
the sleep of the righteous...

187
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,792
...hopheads prowl for marijuana...

188
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:21,911
...not knowing that a man
is coming to stop them:

189
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:25,508
Celebrity crime-stopper, Jack Vincennes.

190
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:29,839
Scourge of grasshoppers
and dope fiends everywhere. "

191
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:31,476
You like it?

192
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,269
Yeah, subtle.

193
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,630
What took you?

194
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:40,758
My partner stopped
to help a damsel in distress.

195
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,911
His priorities are all screwed up.

196
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:45,357
Up to your old tricks again?

197
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:50,549
Hollywood Jack, what brings you
to our humble station house?

198
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,358
What are you doing here?

199
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,471
You know, keeping the streets safe.

200
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,029
Get these two dressed
and book them.

201
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,788
- The party's upstairs.
- I'll be right up.

202
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:06,710
What's that for?

203
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,315
Aren't you watch commander tonight?

204
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:10,390
Yeah. So?

205
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,198
<i>It's from Hush-Hush magazine.</i>

206
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,032
Buy yourself some loafers.

207
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:16,669
No thanks, Jack.
You keep your payoff.

208
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,475
I'm not interested.

209
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,639
What's this?

210
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:28,989
Six spics.

211
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:32,477
The Mexicans who assaulted
Brown and Helenowski.

212
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:35,439
I hear Helenowski bled 6 pints,
Brown's in a coma.

213
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,318
They've got bruises
and muscle pulls.

214
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:38,629
It's not what I heard.

215
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:40,074
Lock them up.

216
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:44,950
Stens, you guys hear what those taco
benders did to Helenowski and Brown?

217
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:50,432
Helenowski lost an eye, and they're
reading Brown his last rites.

218
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:55,277
Should make for a very
merry Christmas for them.

219
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,316
Hey, guys.

220
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:57,510
Guys.

221
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,513
They brought the Mexicans in.

222
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:02,114
They're downstairs.

223
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:07,079
- Let's do it.
- Come on. Let's get them.

224
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:11,478
The party's upstairs.

225
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,713
This doesn't concern you.

226
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:16,789
Come on, guys.

227
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,109
You got work?

228
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:19,429
Go back.

229
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:23,757
- Come on, it's Christmas, help me out.
- Move it!

230
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,116
I just got a few more questions.

231
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,839
You don't have to be here.

232
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:29,190
Go!

233
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,910
You better get your partner
before he kills somebody.

234
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:39,831
Teach him a lesson!
Get him, Stens!

235
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,956
This is for ours, Poncho.

236
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:46,590
Let me through!

237
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,714
He didn't do nothing!

238
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:51,678
What are you looking at?

239
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:55,628
- Tell that Mexican to shut up!
- Move!

240
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:56,989
You're sick!

241
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,155
Stens!

242
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:04,517
- Come on!
- Don't break it up!

243
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,359
Get back! Get back!

244
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,193
Fuck your mother!

245
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,350
Fuck you!

246
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:14,199
Stop! That's an order!

247
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,313
You're all in my report!

248
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,874
"Bloody Christmas. "

249
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,112
The press love to label.

250
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:51,233
This is bigger than the police board.

251
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:55,473
The grand jury's convening.
Indictments may be handed down.

252
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:57,034
Will you testify?

253
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,270
No, sir.

254
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:02,269
District Attorney Loew?

255
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:06,790
You and Officer Stensland
brought the liquor to the station.

256
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,838
Stensland was already drunk.

257
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:14,311
Appearing as a witness against him
could offset the damage to yourself.

258
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,549
I won't testify against him
or anyone else.

259
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:20,071
This man is a disgrace.

260
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:23,875
Your badge and gun, officer.
You're suspended from duty.

261
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,309
Dismissed.

262
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:47,679
We need police witnesses to offset
the damage done to the Department.

263
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:50,952
Justice has to be served.
Of course I'll testify.

264
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:56,832
I'm glad you feel that way.
Most of the men don't.

265
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:59,594
They think silence and integrity
are the same.

266
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,514
Not exactly the image of...

267
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:04,798
...the new LAPD we're creating.

268
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:07,838
Welcome to Los Angeles,
the city of the future.

269
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:10,594
- May I make a suggestion?
- By all means.

270
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:14,879
The public will expect the Department
to sweep this under the carpet.

271
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:16,749
Don't.

272
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:19,999
Shift the guilt to men with
secure pensions.

273
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,798
Force them to retire.

274
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,031
But somebody has to swing.

275
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:30,115
So indict, try and convict
Richard Stensland and Bud White.

276
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,232
Secure them jail time.

277
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,999
The message will be clear.

278
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:39,310
The new LAPD will not tolerate officers
who think they're above the law.

279
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:43,118
Dick Stensland is an embarrassment
as a policeman.

280
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:47,194
He's had rotten fitness reports
from every C.O. He's ever served under.

281
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,351
But White is a valuable officer.

282
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:51,119
White's a mindless thug.

283
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:57,034
He's just a man who can say "yes" to the
questions I asked you the other day.

284
00:17:57,640 --> 00:18:00,438
The Department and the public
need role models.

285
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:03,592
Clean-cut, forthright men
the public can admire.

286
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:05,996
Sergeant...

287
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,158
...I'll promote you...

288
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,839
...to Lieutenant.

289
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:12,992
- Effective immediately.
- Detective Lieutenant.

290
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:16,678
Ed, you're 30.

291
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:20,310
Your father didn't make lieutenant
until he was 33.

292
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:24,309
I know. I also know when he made
lieutenant, it was as a detective.

293
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,795
Before we start polishing our laurels...

294
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:29,508
...it'd look better if we had
a corroborative witness.

295
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,310
That won't be easy to come by.
The men hate a stool pigeon.

296
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:35,039
Jack Vincennes.

297
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,516
He hit one of the Mexicans.

298
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:41,789
A veteran like Vincennes might
admit his own culpability...

299
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:44,390
...but not a fellow officer's.

300
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,759
<i>Jack's the technical advisor
on Badge of Honor.</i>

301
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,433
He lives for it.

302
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,272
That's how to get to him.

303
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,716
I'd like you to observe, Ed.

304
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:01,719
Call Sergeant Vincennes.

305
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:03,839
Bright kid.

306
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:05,957
You may well reap the benefit...

307
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:08,908
...but are you prepared to be despised?

308
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:10,953
Yes, sir, I am.

309
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:13,836
So be it.

310
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:22,070
Sergeant, we'll get right to it.

311
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:26,513
Nine civilian witnesses identified
you as hitting Ezekiel Garcia.

312
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:31,880
But we have a witness who will name
names and testify that you hit back...

313
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,189
...after being hit.

314
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,676
You'll testify against 3 officers...

315
00:19:35,920 --> 00:19:40,436
...who've already earned their pension,
and plead ignorance about the rest.

316
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,711
No thanks. I'm not a snitch.

317
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:46,270
I'll guarantee a slap on the wrist,
a brief suspension...

318
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,637
...followed by a temporary transfer
from Narcotics to Vice.

319
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,673
Transfer out of Vice,
you're back on the show.

320
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:58,395
The show?

321
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:00,518
<i>Badge of Honor.</i>

322
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:04,799
We need to tone down
your profile for a bit.

323
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:11,199
I doubt you've ever taken
a stupid breath. Don't start now.

324
00:20:11,760 --> 00:20:12,954
Okay, I'll do it.

325
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,079
The grand jury hears...

326
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,356
...your testimony tomorrow.
Dismissed.

327
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,111
And so it goes...

328
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:35,278
...Detective Lieutenant.

329
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:39,349
Ace them at the
grand jury tomorrow.

330
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:42,234
Wear a smart-looking suit
and ace them.

331
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,189
And Ed...

332
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,998
...lose the glasses.

333
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:58,593
So you're the stellar witness.

334
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:02,230
I should have known.
What's the Chief throwing you?

335
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:03,510
Throwing me?

336
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:05,552
What's the payoff?

337
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:09,037
You're the payoff expert.
I'm just doing my duty.

338
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:12,670
Come on. You're playing an
angle here, college boy...

339
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:15,912
...so you don't have to hobnob
with the rank and file...

340
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,752
...who'll hate you for snitching.

341
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:20,628
If they make you detective, watch out.

342
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:25,113
Some Bureau guys'll burn in this and
you'll be working with their friends.

343
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:26,190
What about you?

344
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:30,959
I'm snitching 3 old-timers who'll be
fishing in Oregon next week.

345
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:33,111
Next to you, I'm clean...

346
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,475
...and smart.

347
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:37,189
<i>Edmund J. Exley to chambers.</i>

348
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:40,276
And remember...

349
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:44,035
...Bud White will fuck you for this
if it takes the rest of his life.

350
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,193
Captain, what do you want?

351
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:51,469
Call me Dudley.

352
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,638
Dudley...

353
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:54,990
...what do you want?

354
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:59,630
Look, lad, I admire
your refusal to testify...

355
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,911
...and your loyalty to your partner.

356
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,032
I admire you as a policeman...

357
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:08,592
...and your adherence to violence
as a necessary adjunct to the job.

358
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:11,991
And I'm impressed with your
punishment of women-beaters.

359
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,109
Do you hate them?

360
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:17,715
What do you want?

361
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,479
They're yours.

362
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,550
Take them.

363
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,519
There's no bill on me?

364
00:22:30,760 --> 00:22:33,115
- 4 witnesses recanted their testimony.
- Why?

365
00:22:33,360 --> 00:22:34,634
They had a change of heart.

366
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:35,630
And Stensland?

367
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:37,593
Your partner's through.

368
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:39,831
Scapegoat on the Chief's orders.

369
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:41,917
A year from his pension.

370
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:47,997
- Exley?
- Exley got what he wanted.

371
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:51,471
As a politician he exceeds even myself.

372
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:54,959
The Department needs
smart men like Exley...

373
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:56,799
...and direct men...

374
00:22:57,480 --> 00:22:58,549
...like you.

375
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:03,754
Look lad, I need you for
an assignment the Chief's given me.

376
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:06,310
A duty few men are fit for...

377
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:07,999
...but you were born for.

378
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:11,228
You'd be working
out of Homicide at City Hall.

379
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:12,595
Homicide?

380
00:23:13,560 --> 00:23:14,959
Working cases?

381
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:18,594
Your talents lie elsewhere, Wendell.

382
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:20,633
It's a muscle job.

383
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:25,833
You'll do as I say and ask no questions.
Do you follow my drift?

384
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:28,598
In Technicolor, sir.

385
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:34,112
<i>"Meet Tony Brancato
and Anthony Trombino...</i>

386
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:37,670
<i>...two rising lieutenants
in the Mickey Cohen rackets.</i>

387
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:40,673
<i>With the dapper little gent in prison...</i>

388
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:44,039
<i>...who knows how far they'll go?
The sky's the limit.</i>

389
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,396
<i>Oh, well. "</i>

390
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:08,278
<i>"Meet Deuce Perkins,
Mickey Cohen's narcotics lieutenant.</i>

391
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,839
<i>Could he be behind the hits?</i>

392
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:13,239
<i>Is he consolidating
organized crime power?</i>

393
00:24:19,120 --> 00:24:20,712
<i>I suppose not.</i>

394
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,479
<i>One thing's for sure:</i>

395
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:30,792
<i>2- man triggers are punching the tickets
on the Mickster's muscle. "</i>

396
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:43,475
<i>"Meanwhile, rumor has it the LAPD...</i>

397
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:48,350
<i>...has set up a not-so-Welcome Wagon
to dishearten the criminal element...</i>

398
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:51,717
<i>...from filling the void left by
Mickey's absence.</i>

399
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:54,758
<i>When I know more, dear readers,
so will you.</i>

400
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,560
<i>Off the record, on the q. T...</i>

401
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,399
<i>...and very...</i>

402
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,358
<i>...Hush-Hush. "</i>

403
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:06,308
<i>With Mickey Cohen in prison,
Los Angeles is organized-crime-free.</i>

404
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:08,278
<i>The Chief wants to keep it that way.</i>

405
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:12,438
In Cleveland, you're an
organized crime associate...

406
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:16,309
...in desperate need of re-education
in the ways of polite society.

407
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:20,352
I hear things.

408
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:22,431
Like those 2-men shooter teams.

409
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,636
They're 86ing Cohen's lieutenants.

410
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,313
What do you want?

411
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:28,838
We want you to go home.

412
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,872
Picture-book smut, men.

413
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:38,635
There's been a bunch of this
found at crime scenes lately.

414
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:41,713
Quality ranges from piss-poor...

415
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:43,716
...to very well done.

416
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:46,591
Look who's back from suspension.

417
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:49,271
We're honored, Sergeant Jack.

418
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:52,751
Look at that.
The Great Jerk-Off Case of 1953.

419
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:55,190
Is there someplace you'd rather be?

420
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:58,792
Yeah, working Narcotics,
looking for Cohen's missing H.

421
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:02,959
Yeah, finding 25 pounds of heroin
would get you plenty of ink.

422
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:06,158
You should've thought of that
before Bloody Christmas.

423
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:10,749
Make a major case. It's the only way
you'll get out of here.

424
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,639
Dismissed, gentlemen.

425
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:23,397
Go get the facts, Jack.

426
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:25,312
Just the facts.

427
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,874
<i>Whatever you desire.</i>

428
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:36,754
Hi. I'd like to get a delivery
to Beverly Hills.

429
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:38,030
<i>I don't know you.</i>

430
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:42,832
A friend just gave me this number
and I wanted to find out if there was...

431
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:47,629
Would you grab a reverse directory
and shag a name and address for me?

432
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,718
Crestview-2239.

433
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:58,916
<i>Hush-Hush, off the record, on the q. T.</i>

434
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:00,913
Sid, it's Vincennes.

435
00:27:01,280 --> 00:27:04,397
Jackie, you back on narco?
I need some good copy.

436
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,557
I have something going with Vice.

437
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:08,273
Something juicy for the Sidster?

438
00:27:08,520 --> 00:27:10,670
<i>Tracking porn.
Arty, high-class stuff.</i>

439
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:13,793
<i>Know about Fleur-de-Lis?
Slogan's "Whatever you desire. "</i>

440
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:15,593
<i>No, I've heard bupkes.</i>

441
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:19,270
Get me some narco skinny.
I want to do an all-hophead issue.

442
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:23,235
<i>Shvartze jazz musicians and movie stars.
You like it?</i>

443
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:24,839
I'll talk to you later.

444
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:27,475
- What do you got?
- The number's not assigned.

445
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:28,750
Thanks, Ginger.

446
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,789
A bootleg.

447
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:41,635
Take it easy.

448
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,274
Tough break, Stens.

449
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:45,517
We're going to miss you.

450
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:47,359
Raw deal, Stensland.

451
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:52,318
Here comes the snitch.

452
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,599
Sorry about that, Lieutenant.

453
00:28:20,960 --> 00:28:22,632
Stay out of trouble, Bud.

454
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:27,196
I got some time.
I'll buy you a drink.

455
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:29,391
Rain check. I got a hot date.

456
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:33,430
Who is she and
what did you arrest her for?

457
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,188
It's confidential.

458
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:40,111
<i>Like that magazine that
Vincennes scams for. Hush-Hush.</i>

459
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:42,998
I'll see you later in the week.

460
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:45,398
We'll do the town, on me.

461
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:48,513
Yeah. I'll bring
my wallet just in case.

462
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,791
- See you tomorrow.
- Hang on a minute.

463
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:56,999
I'll walk down with you.

464
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:07,789
Punk kid. Who is he
trying to impress?

465
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:09,869
Yeah, I wonder.

466
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:12,310
Got himself a real career going.

467
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:18,670
<i>Sergeant Williams, pick up, please.</i>

468
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,439
<i>Sergeant Williams?</i>

469
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:27,234
<i>Is there anybody up there in Homicide?</i>

470
00:29:28,320 --> 00:29:29,719
<i>Anybody there?</i>

471
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:32,955
Lieutenant Exley.

472
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:35,111
<i>You've got a homicide downtown.</i>

473
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:38,119
<i>- The Nite Owl Coffee Shop.
- I got it.</i>

474
00:29:38,440 --> 00:29:39,429
It's mine.

475
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:53,194
At least one person's dead.
I stopped for coffee...

476
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:56,120
No one comes through
the front door. Understand?

477
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:32,195
I want barricades both ends
of the street. Make sure...

478
00:31:32,640 --> 00:31:34,471
I took the call. It's my case.

479
00:31:35,120 --> 00:31:37,111
You don't want it and you can't have it.

480
00:31:37,480 --> 00:31:38,310
I took the call.

481
00:31:38,680 --> 00:31:39,635
It's mine.

482
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:42,478
I'll make you my second-in-command.

483
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:44,398
Captain, over here, please.

484
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:52,712
The cook drew a gun and set it off.
The rest died in the men's room.

485
00:31:58,520 --> 00:32:01,876
We got a total of 15 spent
12-gauge Remington shotgun shells.

486
00:32:02,240 --> 00:32:06,074
I'm betting 3 men, 5-shot capacity
pumps, all of them emptying once.

487
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:09,159
Excuse me, we got an I.D.
On one of the victims.

488
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:10,989
It's Dick Stensland.

489
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:15,955
At first, I thought
she was Rita Hayworth.

490
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:17,594
Yeah, me too.

491
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,911
Hell of a way to avoid prison.

492
00:32:39,280 --> 00:32:40,429
What happened?

493
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:43,349
Appears 3 men held up a coffee shop.

494
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:46,359
The guy at the register pulled a.38,
so they killed him.

495
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,478
Then they killed everyone else.

496
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:54,193
Lieutenant, we're ready
with that Nite Owl I.D.

497
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:01,352
Is this your daughter?

498
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:03,673
I don't know.

499
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:06,949
We know this is difficult.
Take your time.

500
00:33:08,720 --> 00:33:10,756
It seems like my Susan.

501
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:13,753
But my Susan was a blonde,
not a redhead.

502
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:15,792
When was the last time you saw her?

503
00:33:16,360 --> 00:33:18,157
Just before Christmas.

504
00:33:18,800 --> 00:33:21,553
We'd fought.
I didn't like her boyfriend.

505
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,229
Mrs. Lefferts...

506
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:25,830
...does your daughter have
any distinguishing marks?

507
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:29,673
<i>You got the wrong idea, mister.
I'm fine.</i>

508
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:33,518
She has a birthmark on her hip.

509
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:40,593
It's her.

510
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:43,316
My baby.

511
00:33:46,520 --> 00:33:48,112
I'm sorry, Mrs. Lefferts.

512
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:51,555
Who's in charge of this investigation?

513
00:33:52,080 --> 00:33:53,433
Captain Smith and myself. Why?

514
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,274
<i>"The Nite Owl Massacre. "</i>

515
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:59,198
Hyperbole aside...

516
00:33:59,560 --> 00:34:02,916
...this is a heinous crime
that requires swift resolution.

517
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:04,830
Six victims.

518
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:07,668
One of them, one of our own.
Dick Stensland.

519
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:11,959
He was a Nite Owl regular,
in the wrong place at the wrong time.

520
00:34:12,560 --> 00:34:14,198
Robbery is the likely motive.

521
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:18,752
We have rubber glove smears
on the register and forensics...

522
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:22,590
...tend toward a trio of shooters.
We do have one hot lead.

523
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:24,838
Three Negro juveniles...

524
00:34:25,200 --> 00:34:28,510
...were seen discharging shotguns
last night in Griffith Park.

525
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:32,634
A park ranger I.D.'d them as driving
a 1948-1950 Mercury coupe...

526
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,115
...maroon in color.

527
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:38,116
An hour ago a canvassing crew
turned up a news vendor...

528
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:41,876
...who saw a maroon Merc coupe
parked by the Nite Owl at 1 a. m.

529
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:45,956
DMV has come up with
a registration list of Merc coupes.

530
00:34:47,280 --> 00:34:51,478
48 two-man teams will shake
three names apiece.

531
00:34:52,240 --> 00:34:54,629
Interrogations will be led by
Lt. Edmund Exley.

532
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,308
Enough on that!

533
00:35:02,520 --> 00:35:05,876
Gentlemen, just go out and get them.
Use all necessary force.

534
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:09,196
The people of Los Angeles demand it.

535
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:10,949
Dismissed.

536
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:16,111
Why not just put a bounty on them?

537
00:35:23,240 --> 00:35:26,152
- Ready to roll?
- You take them. I got something to do.

538
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:28,198
What if one of these names...?

539
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:29,879
Get somebody else.

540
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:32,791
I got our assignments, Big V.

541
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:35,913
If we go by this list,
we'll never make this collar.

542
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:40,114
I got a guy who knows what happens
south of Jefferson. He'll put us at 50-50.

543
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:44,879
What are you doing? That's the same
thing that got you in trouble before.

544
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:46,468
I'll take those odds.

545
00:35:50,520 --> 00:35:51,794
We got it from here.

546
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:56,315
You should bring along
a photographer.

547
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:04,397
I need an address on a customer
of yours. Her name is Lynn.

548
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:06,398
- That's all I got to go on?
- Yeah.

549
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:09,070
You already know who I mean,
so cough it up.

550
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:12,472
<i>There's a billing address
and a delivery address.</i>

551
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:39,752
Are you Pierce Patchett?

552
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:42,035
I am.

553
00:36:44,080 --> 00:36:47,914
Are you soliciting for police charities?
Last time you called my office.

554
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:51,113
Go on down to the driveway.
We'll talk there.

555
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:03,153
What can I do for you?

556
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:07,630
- Where were you last night?
- I was here hosting a party.

557
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:10,873
Tell me about Dick Stensland.

558
00:37:11,240 --> 00:37:13,196
I don't know him, Mr...?

559
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:14,834
Officer White.

560
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:17,075
You know Sue Lefferts?

561
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:19,636
You know I do.
You saw me with her.

562
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:22,839
How did you find me?

563
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:27,434
Nick's Liquor. This is where
Lynn Bracken's booze bills go.

564
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,199
Of course.

565
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:34,036
Sue Lefferts died at the Nite Owl.

566
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:36,239
I'm investigating.

567
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:39,799
Everything all right?

568
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:42,032
Fine, Phillip, thank you.

569
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:48,469
What happened to the other guy?
Buzz.

570
00:37:48,880 --> 00:37:50,950
Buzz Meeks no longer works for me.

571
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:53,550
Lefferts looked beat-up Christmas Eve
but didn't act it. Why?

572
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:57,833
I think she'd been hit in the face
with a tennis racket. She is... was...

573
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:59,349
...a big doubles fan.

574
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:02,993
You're a known associate of a woman
killed in a mass murder.

575
00:38:04,640 --> 00:38:07,950
- Want to go downtown to discuss it?
- Is this official?

576
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:13,072
Somehow I have the feeling
this is more personal with you.

577
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:17,679
All right, then...

578
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:22,713
...are you concerned about criminal
matters peripheral to the murders?

579
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:26,197
- Not at the moment.
- So you're not obligated to report them.

580
00:38:28,560 --> 00:38:30,551
Why were Lefferts' eyes black?

581
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:33,514
I needed a Rita Hayworth
to fill out my little studio.

582
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:34,790
What little studio?

583
00:38:35,160 --> 00:38:38,516
Well, there's Gardner, Russell,
Monroe, Turner...

584
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:40,916
Lynn Bracken is my Veronica Lake.

585
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:43,755
I use girls that look like movie stars.

586
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:46,509
Sometimes I employ a plastic surgeon.

587
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:49,395
When the work was done,
that's when you saw us.

588
00:38:50,280 --> 00:38:51,918
It's why her mom couldn't I.D. Her.

589
00:38:53,480 --> 00:38:54,833
Jesus fucking Christ.

590
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,911
No, Pierce Morehouse Patchett.

591
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:02,556
I sense you're on your best behavior,
but that's all I'm saying.

592
00:39:03,080 --> 00:39:04,911
If you persist,
we'll meet with my attorney.

593
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:08,076
Would you like Lynn Bracken's address?

594
00:39:08,440 --> 00:39:09,873
I got her address.

595
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:13,071
Find Susan's killer, Mr. White.

596
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,631
I'll give you a handsome reward.

597
00:39:20,840 --> 00:39:21,636
Whatever you desire!

598
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,479
<i>I know you're not asleep.</i>

599
00:39:33,840 --> 00:39:35,592
<i>What do you want?</i>

600
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:37,393
<i>My 5 bucks.</i>

601
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:39,876
<i>It was the only one I had.</i>

602
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,229
Right now?

603
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:44,070
Hey, dollface,
tell him to leave us alone.

604
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:46,510
I understand.
Okay, fine.

605
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:49,069
Oh, baby...

606
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:51,595
...bad news.

607
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:52,870
You have to go.

608
00:39:53,240 --> 00:39:54,195
Go?

609
00:39:54,680 --> 00:39:57,831
Something very important has come up
and you have to go.

610
00:39:58,200 --> 00:39:59,838
I'll make it up to you.

611
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:02,509
I will, I promise.
Excuse me.

612
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,359
Is it the cops?

613
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:11,909
Miss Bracken...

614
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:13,030
...I'm Officer White.

615
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:15,755
I've been expecting you,
just not this soon.

616
00:40:16,120 --> 00:40:18,475
Pierce called.
He told me what happened to Sue.

617
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:21,673
Everything all right, doll?
Want me to get rid of him?

618
00:40:22,160 --> 00:40:22,910
Hit the road.

619
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:26,679
Maybe I will...

620
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:28,599
...maybe I won't.

621
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:32,430
LAPD, shitbird. Get out or
I'll have your wife come get you.

622
00:40:48,440 --> 00:40:49,793
- Officer.
- Councilman.

623
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:10,997
- Would you care for a drink?
- Yeah, Scotch straight.

624
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:20,076
I was friendly with Sue Lefferts,
but we weren't friends.

625
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:21,709
Know what I mean?

626
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:23,673
You sorry she's dead?

627
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:26,839
Of course I am.

628
00:41:27,240 --> 00:41:28,912
What kind of question is that?

629
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:33,156
You know why Pierce
is humoring you?

630
00:41:33,520 --> 00:41:35,670
Use words like that,
you might make me mad.

631
00:41:36,080 --> 00:41:37,069
But do you know?

632
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:38,475
Yeah, I know.

633
00:41:39,600 --> 00:41:41,192
Patchett's running whores...

634
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:44,352
...cut to look like movie stars.

635
00:41:44,720 --> 00:41:47,837
And judging by his address,
something bigger on the side.

636
00:41:48,200 --> 00:41:49,872
He doesn't want any attention.

637
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:53,556
That's right. Our motives are selfish
so we're cooperating.

638
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:56,559
So cooperate. Why was
Susan Lefferts at the Nite Owl?

639
00:41:57,040 --> 00:41:59,395
I don't know. I never heard of
the Nite Owl till today.

640
00:41:59,760 --> 00:42:00,590
How'd she meet Patchett?

641
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:02,359
Pierce meets people.

642
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:06,354
Sue had dreams of Hollywood
and this is how they turned out.

643
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:10,475
Thanks to Pierce,
we still get to act a little.

644
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:13,236
Tell me about Pierce.

645
00:42:13,720 --> 00:42:15,551
He's waiting for you to mention money.

646
00:42:16,880 --> 00:42:19,758
- Want some advice, Miss Bracken?
- It's Lynn.

647
00:42:20,240 --> 00:42:21,355
Miss Bracken...

648
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:24,550
...don't ever try to fucking bribe me...

649
00:42:24,920 --> 00:42:27,115
...or I'll have you and Patchett
in shit up to your ears.

650
00:42:28,240 --> 00:42:30,515
I remember you from Christmas Eve.

651
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:34,718
You have a thing
for helping women, don't you?

652
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:37,192
Maybe I'm just fucking curious.

653
00:42:37,640 --> 00:42:40,712
- You say "fuck" a lot.
- You fuck for money.

654
00:42:41,040 --> 00:42:44,430
There's blood on your shirt.
Is that an integral part of your job?

655
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:46,193
- Yeah.
- Do you enjoy it?

656
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:47,390
When they deserve it.

657
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,034
Did they deserve it today?

658
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:51,630
I'm not sure.

659
00:42:52,040 --> 00:42:53,234
- But you did it anyway.
- Yeah.

660
00:42:54,120 --> 00:42:56,111
Like the half dozen guys
you screwed today.

661
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:59,351
Actually, it was only two.

662
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:03,518
You're different, Officer White.

663
00:43:03,880 --> 00:43:08,078
You're the first man in years who didn't
tell me I look like Veronica Lake.

664
00:43:08,440 --> 00:43:09,998
You look better than Veronica Lake.

665
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:16,310
Pierce Patchett?

666
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:20,594
He takes a cut of our earnings
and invests it for us.

667
00:43:20,960 --> 00:43:23,793
He doesn't let us use narcotics
and he doesn't abuse us.

668
00:43:24,240 --> 00:43:27,835
Can your policeman's mentality
grasp those contradictions?

669
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:32,070
He had you cut
to look like Veronica Lake.

670
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:33,236
No.

671
00:43:33,960 --> 00:43:36,633
I'm really a brunette,
but the rest is me.

672
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:40,875
And that's all the news
that's fit to print.

673
00:43:42,160 --> 00:43:43,957
It's nice meeting you.

674
00:43:48,560 --> 00:43:50,676
- I'd like to see you again.
- For a date...

675
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:52,075
...or an appointment?

676
00:43:54,120 --> 00:43:55,109
I don't know.

677
00:43:55,520 --> 00:43:58,910
- If it's a date, what's your first name?
- Forget I asked.

678
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:01,393
It was a mistake.

679
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:22,519
Leonard Bidwell?

680
00:44:23,720 --> 00:44:25,517
Come down here and talk to us.

681
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:28,749
How's the left these days?

682
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:30,270
What's it to you?

683
00:44:30,640 --> 00:44:32,073
I saw you fight Kid Gavilan.

684
00:44:32,560 --> 00:44:33,993
I like your style.

685
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:38,192
What do you want, Mr. Policeman?

686
00:44:39,080 --> 00:44:41,389
You got a brother in Folsom.
I put him there.

687
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:42,590
Until 1970.

688
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:44,757
How'd you like to make it 1960?

689
00:44:45,160 --> 00:44:47,310
I know the judge,
and Lieutenant Exley...

690
00:44:47,680 --> 00:44:49,591
...is good friends with the D.A.

691
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:55,317
We're looking for 3 colored guys
who like to pop off shotguns.

692
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:57,557
One owns a maroon Mercury coupe.

693
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:00,878
- Want me to snitch?
- Want to buy your brother 10 years?

694
00:45:01,240 --> 00:45:02,878
- It was 10 years?
- 10 years.

695
00:45:03,240 --> 00:45:06,198
You don't have to say anything,
just look at this list...

696
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:07,959
...and point.

697
00:45:10,320 --> 00:45:12,117
He's bad, so I'll just tell you.

698
00:45:12,720 --> 00:45:13,835
Sugar Ray Collins.

699
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:16,236
Drives a maroon '49 coupe.

700
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:18,353
Beautiful ride.

701
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:22,993
Don't know about shotguns,
but he gets his thrills killing dogs.

702
00:45:23,440 --> 00:45:24,555
He's righteous trash.

703
00:45:25,040 --> 00:45:27,952
Look at that. It's five minutes
from here. Thanks.

704
00:45:30,160 --> 00:45:31,479
I'll hear from you...

705
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:33,828
...about my brother?

706
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:36,236
Keep it up, Lenny. Up.

707
00:45:42,120 --> 00:45:44,156
There it is.
It's in the back.

708
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:03,309
- One of ours.
- Shit, somebody beat us here.

709
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:10,349
Damn it.

710
00:46:10,960 --> 00:46:12,154
My glasses.

711
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:13,589
You're kidding.

712
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:16,917
Just don't shoot me.

713
00:46:25,520 --> 00:46:27,112
What are you doing here?

714
00:46:28,200 --> 00:46:29,713
We were in the neighborhood.

715
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:33,396
- What do you got?
- Three 12-gauge pumps.

716
00:46:33,680 --> 00:46:34,351
And cash.

717
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:39,108
<i>So long, Vice.
Badge of Honor, here I come.</i>

718
00:46:39,480 --> 00:46:41,038
Fuck you! This is our collar.

719
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:42,355
Quiet!

720
00:46:42,720 --> 00:46:46,030
I'm ranking officer here.
We go as a team. End of story.

721
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,116
Right.

722
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:54,509
How many ways in?

723
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:56,871
Only one. Up the stairs.

724
00:46:58,320 --> 00:47:00,117
He's very serious.

725
00:47:14,200 --> 00:47:14,996
Police!

726
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:16,195
Don't shoot!

727
00:47:18,120 --> 00:47:20,111
- Don't move.
- Shut up!

728
00:47:20,360 --> 00:47:21,509
Anxious, aren't you?

729
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:22,790
Don't kill them.

730
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:26,439
Back, back, back!

731
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:28,875
Get off me!

732
00:47:30,160 --> 00:47:31,479
Against the wall!

733
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:33,432
- Put your hands up!
- Get over there.

734
00:47:34,640 --> 00:47:36,232
Shut up!
Hands behind your back!

735
00:47:37,520 --> 00:47:38,396
So...

736
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:41,548
...how's it feel
getting out of the office?

737
00:47:47,480 --> 00:47:48,879
This came from forensics.

738
00:47:49,240 --> 00:47:50,559
"Burning clothes...

739
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:53,708
...Casitas Youth Camp... "

740
00:47:57,080 --> 00:47:58,718
It's crowded in here, White.

741
00:47:59,360 --> 00:48:00,998
These guys killed Stensland.

742
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:19,634
The ejection marks on the shells
fired from the shotguns...

743
00:48:20,000 --> 00:48:22,833
...are identical to those on the
shell casings found at the Nite Owl.

744
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:25,032
I want confessions, Edmund.

745
00:48:25,480 --> 00:48:27,391
A night's stewing
has softened them up.

746
00:48:28,680 --> 00:48:30,033
I'll break them, sir.

747
00:48:49,560 --> 00:48:52,313
Are you sure golden boy
is up to the task, Cap?

748
00:48:53,040 --> 00:48:55,793
I think you'd be surprised
what the lad is capable of.

749
00:48:58,160 --> 00:48:59,991
