01:10:50,320 --> 01:10:51,275
Kid?

998
01:10:58,960 --> 01:11:01,315
Come on, you don't have to do this...

999
01:11:31,840 --> 01:11:34,035
Thank you for what you did for me...

1000
01:11:34,360 --> 01:11:36,794
...for killing those animals
who raped me.

1001
01:11:37,200 --> 01:11:39,839
Will you thank Officer White
for me, please?

1002
01:11:40,080 --> 01:11:41,035
Sure.

1003
01:11:42,560 --> 01:11:46,314
Seeing him come through the door
is about the only thing I remember.

1004
01:11:46,560 --> 01:11:47,549
Thank God.

1005
01:11:48,600 --> 01:11:51,398
You remember what time
the Negroes left you?

1006
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:54,632
In your statement, you said
they left you at midnight.

1007
01:11:54,880 --> 01:11:55,915
They might have.

1008
01:12:01,240 --> 01:12:02,514
They "might" have?

1009
01:12:02,800 --> 01:12:06,190
I don't know what time they left me.
I wanted them dead.

1010
01:12:06,680 --> 01:12:09,831
Would anyone care that they
raped a Mexican girl...

1011
01:12:10,160 --> 01:12:12,958
...if they hadn't killed those
white people at the Nite Owl?

1012
01:12:14,000 --> 01:12:16,150
I did what I had to do for justice.

1013
01:12:17,040 --> 01:12:18,268
Exley, over here.

1014
01:12:18,520 --> 01:12:19,509
Smile, Inez.

1015
01:12:21,160 --> 01:12:22,832
Is he your hero?

1016
01:12:23,520 --> 01:12:27,638
Fellas, how about this? " Rape Victim
Wheeled Out by Nite Owl Hero. "

1017
01:12:33,200 --> 01:12:35,191
All they get is Veronica Lake.

1018
01:12:37,440 --> 01:12:39,556
I get Lynn Margaret Bracken.

1019
01:12:50,320 --> 01:12:51,309
"Bisbee"?

1020
01:12:53,560 --> 01:12:54,913
I grew up there.

1021
01:12:57,040 --> 01:13:01,238
I'm going back in a couple of years,
open up a dress shop.

1022
01:13:03,280 --> 01:13:06,238
The girls in Bisbee
need a little glamour.

1023
01:13:11,680 --> 01:13:13,113
Where'd this come from?

1024
01:13:14,880 --> 01:13:18,589
I was 12. My dad went after my mother
with a bottle. I got in the way.

1025
01:13:20,640 --> 01:13:22,039
So you saved her.

1026
01:13:23,520 --> 01:13:24,635
Not for long.

1027
01:13:27,760 --> 01:13:30,752
- I'm sorry. It's none of my business.
- He tied me to the radiator.

1028
01:13:31,640 --> 01:13:34,598
I watched him beat my mother to death
with a tire iron...

1029
01:13:37,040 --> 01:13:38,393
...and he left me there.

1030
01:13:40,920 --> 01:13:43,673
Three days before
a truant officer found us.

1031
01:13:46,840 --> 01:13:48,512
They never found the old man.

1032
01:13:57,600 --> 01:13:59,397
Is that why you became a cop?

1033
01:14:00,240 --> 01:14:01,468
To get even?

1034
01:14:03,120 --> 01:14:04,109
Maybe.

1035
01:14:06,040 --> 01:14:07,359
Do you like it?

1036
01:14:10,640 --> 01:14:11,834
I used to.

1037
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:16,519
Now it's all strong-arm,
sitting duck stuff.

1038
01:14:20,080 --> 01:14:23,755
If I could get a chance to work
Homicide like a real detective...

1039
01:14:26,000 --> 01:14:28,594
That prick, Exley.
He shot the wrong guys.

1040
01:14:29,240 --> 01:14:33,597
Whoever killed Stensland's still around.
I know it in here. I know it.

1041
01:14:34,320 --> 01:14:36,038
Something's wrong
with the Nite Owl.

1042
01:14:36,440 --> 01:14:38,396
I just can't prove it, that's all.

1043
01:14:39,680 --> 01:14:41,432
I'm not smart enough.

1044
01:14:43,480 --> 01:14:46,517
I'm just the guy they bring in
to scare the other guy shitless.

1045
01:14:49,720 --> 01:14:50,994
You're wrong.

1046
01:14:51,920 --> 01:14:54,229
You found Patchett. You found me.

1047
01:14:54,720 --> 01:14:56,358
You're smart enough.

1048
01:15:07,640 --> 01:15:10,552
Bud White. What brings you
down to the basement?

1049
01:15:14,200 --> 01:15:16,031
A couple of Nite Owl questions.

1050
01:15:16,280 --> 01:15:19,238
Don't know if you read the papers,
but that case is closed.

1051
01:15:21,200 --> 01:15:22,918
Anything bother you about it?

1052
01:15:23,640 --> 01:15:27,155
The fact that the pack-up boys haven't
hauled this shit out of here yet.

1053
01:15:31,680 --> 01:15:35,514
The suspects' 3 shotguns match
the strike marks on the shell casings.

1054
01:15:36,600 --> 01:15:38,192
What more do you want?

1055
01:15:49,600 --> 01:15:51,352
There's blood on the wall here.

1056
01:15:51,960 --> 01:15:54,315
I thought everyone got shot
in the men's room.

1057
01:15:54,560 --> 01:15:56,755
That is Stensland's blood.

1058
01:15:58,840 --> 01:16:02,549
Blow to the head. Probably unconscious
when they dragged him in the john.

1059
01:16:04,120 --> 01:16:05,394
They hit anyone else?

1060
01:16:05,640 --> 01:16:08,712
No, but he was a cop.
Probably tried to do something.

1061
01:16:12,480 --> 01:16:15,870
Grilled cheese, black coffee.
Someone was sitting next to him.

1062
01:16:19,840 --> 01:16:21,478
2 of the victims were women?

1063
01:16:21,760 --> 01:16:25,469
Yeah, Patti DeLuca, the night shift
waitress, and a Susan Lefferts.

1064
01:16:30,040 --> 01:16:31,678
Susan Lefferts.

1065
01:16:33,360 --> 01:16:34,679
What about her?

1066
01:16:37,760 --> 01:16:38,988
You're welcome!

1067
01:16:44,880 --> 01:16:45,995
Mrs. Lefferts?

1068
01:16:46,360 --> 01:16:48,112
I'm Officer White, LAPD.

1069
01:16:50,960 --> 01:16:54,111
Tell me about the boyfriend.
The one you mentioned at the coroner's.

1070
01:16:54,360 --> 01:16:56,590
Susie, I told you
I didn't approve.

1071
01:16:57,200 --> 01:17:01,318
He was too old for you.
And you let him be fresh with me.

1072
01:17:03,120 --> 01:17:05,315
They came here one day
when I wasn't home.

1073
01:17:05,880 --> 01:17:07,472
Mrs. Jensen next door said...

1074
01:17:07,840 --> 01:17:11,116
...she saw Susie's boyfriend
and another man...

1075
01:17:11,480 --> 01:17:13,072
...and she heard a ruckus.

1076
01:17:13,840 --> 01:17:14,875
What was his name?

1077
01:17:15,160 --> 01:17:17,594
We weren't properly introduced.

1078
01:17:18,320 --> 01:17:20,390
He had a nickname, Muns or Luns.

1079
01:17:20,760 --> 01:17:23,115
Stens? Was it Stens?

1080
01:17:23,360 --> 01:17:24,395
Maybe.

1081
01:17:24,760 --> 01:17:26,671
- I don't know.
- Look at this picture.

1082
01:17:30,360 --> 01:17:31,395
That's him.

1083
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:32,755
That's him.

1084
01:17:37,920 --> 01:17:40,150
You said a neighbor heard a ruckus.

1085
01:17:40,720 --> 01:17:41,596
Outside?

1086
01:17:41,840 --> 01:17:42,750
Inside?

1087
01:17:43,960 --> 01:17:45,075
Outside.

1088
01:17:45,440 --> 01:17:49,115
And then Mrs. Jensen said
they kept going under the house.

1089
01:17:53,160 --> 01:17:55,355
You have to leave now, Officer.

1090
01:17:56,640 --> 01:17:59,871
- What's through here?
- Just a room full of old things.

1091
01:18:00,120 --> 01:18:01,872
Don't move that.

1092
01:18:04,280 --> 01:18:07,716
Don't mind the smell.
I think a rat died behind the wall.

1093
01:18:09,040 --> 01:18:10,393
My Susie was a good girl.

1094
01:18:11,120 --> 01:18:14,032
She was never in any
kind of trouble at all.

1095
01:19:22,520 --> 01:19:24,670
<i>"Leland Meeks. "
Never heard of you.</i>

1096
01:19:25,040 --> 01:19:26,439
<i>They call me Buzz.</i>

1097
01:19:33,240 --> 01:19:34,389
Was it a rat?

1098
01:19:35,280 --> 01:19:36,952
Yeah, a great big one.

1099
01:19:39,280 --> 01:19:40,235
Here.

1100
01:19:41,200 --> 01:19:43,031
Compliments of the Police Department.

1101
01:19:59,480 --> 01:20:02,153
Stomach of the week
from a motel homicide.

1102
01:20:02,400 --> 01:20:05,836
Unemployed actor had frankfurter,
french fries, alcohol and sperm.

1103
01:20:06,080 --> 01:20:08,355
Hell of a last supper,
don't you think?

1104
01:20:08,600 --> 01:20:11,398
Anything bothering you
about the Nite Owl case?

1105
01:20:11,920 --> 01:20:13,797
The fact that you guys
won't let it go.

1106
01:20:14,960 --> 01:20:18,396
- What do you mean?
- Bud White grilled me on it today.

1107
01:20:19,520 --> 01:20:20,589
Bud White?

1108
01:20:21,320 --> 01:20:23,151
He's not as dumb as I thought.

1109
01:20:25,440 --> 01:20:27,954
Did he say where he was going?

1110
01:20:39,960 --> 01:20:41,678
Let my daughter rest in peace!

1111
01:20:41,920 --> 01:20:43,956
I just want to ask a few questions.

1112
01:20:44,200 --> 01:20:46,475
Officer White already checked
under the house.

1113
01:20:47,040 --> 01:20:48,075
Under the house?

1114
01:20:48,800 --> 01:20:50,916
- Where?
- Out back.

1115
01:20:52,440 --> 01:20:53,953
All he found was rodents.

1116
01:20:57,200 --> 01:21:00,954
I need an I.D. On this as soon as
possible. Talk only to me on this one.

1117
01:21:04,800 --> 01:21:05,710
I need your help.

1118
01:21:05,960 --> 01:21:09,191
I'm busy. Why don't you ask
your boys in Homicide?

1119
01:21:12,000 --> 01:21:14,594
I can't. I need someone
outside of Homicide.

1120
01:21:15,280 --> 01:21:17,919
I want you to tail Bud White.

1121
01:21:19,360 --> 01:21:21,430
Do me a favor. Leave me alone.

1122
01:21:22,600 --> 01:21:24,795
You make the 3 Negroes
for the Nite Owl killings?

1123
01:21:28,000 --> 01:21:28,796
What?

1124
01:21:29,120 --> 01:21:30,394
It's a simple question.

1125
01:21:32,520 --> 01:21:35,114
Why in the world
do you want to dig deeper...

1126
01:21:35,480 --> 01:21:37,198
...into the Nite Owl killings...

1127
01:21:37,560 --> 01:21:38,595
...Lieutenant?

1128
01:21:42,320 --> 01:21:43,639
Rollo Tomasi.

1129
01:21:45,760 --> 01:21:47,671
Is there more or do I have to guess?

1130
01:21:50,720 --> 01:21:52,676
Rollo was a purse snatcher.

1131
01:21:57,040 --> 01:21:58,917
My father ran into him off-duty.

1132
01:22:00,960 --> 01:22:03,793
He shot my father 6 times
and got away clean.

1133
01:22:05,360 --> 01:22:06,918
No one knew who he was.

1134
01:22:07,880 --> 01:22:09,836
I made the name up
to give him personality.

1135
01:22:11,640 --> 01:22:12,629
Your point?

1136
01:22:13,280 --> 01:22:15,794
Rollo Tomasi's the reason
I became a cop.

1137
01:22:16,680 --> 01:22:19,911
I wanted to catch the guys who
thought they could get away with it.

1138
01:22:21,440 --> 01:22:23,112
It was about justice.

1139
01:22:24,080 --> 01:22:26,833
Then somewhere along the way
I lost sight of that.

1140
01:22:30,920 --> 01:22:32,114
Why'd you become a cop?

1141
01:22:42,320 --> 01:22:43,878
I don't remember.

1142
01:22:50,440 --> 01:22:51,589
What do you want?

1143
01:22:52,320 --> 01:22:53,799
I want to solve this.

1144
01:22:54,520 --> 01:22:56,033
Nite Owl was solved.

1145
01:22:58,880 --> 01:22:59,995
I want to do it right.

1146
01:23:00,800 --> 01:23:02,950
Even if it means
paying the consequences?

1147
01:23:06,440 --> 01:23:08,078
All right, college boy, I'll help.

1148
01:23:08,600 --> 01:23:11,114
But there's a case your boys
in Homicide don't care about.

1149
01:23:11,480 --> 01:23:15,109
They think it's just another
Hollywood "homo" -cide. But I don't.

1150
01:23:16,080 --> 01:23:19,072
You help me with mine,
I'll help you with yours.

1151
01:23:19,640 --> 01:23:20,470
Deal?

1152
01:23:21,560 --> 01:23:22,310
Deal.

1153
01:23:53,520 --> 01:23:55,397
Johnny Stompanato.

1154
01:23:56,640 --> 01:23:59,234
<i>Officer Wendell White.
How's tricks, paesano?</i>

1155
01:23:59,600 --> 01:24:01,033
<i>I ain't your paesano.</i>

1156
01:24:01,920 --> 01:24:03,876
I ain't in the snitch business anymore.

1157
01:24:04,200 --> 01:24:06,156
You know a guy named Buzz Meeks?

1158
01:24:07,320 --> 01:24:08,958
Works for Pierce Patchett.

1159
01:24:09,640 --> 01:24:10,675
Should I?

1160
01:24:12,120 --> 01:24:14,714
You're muscle for hire.
Meeks is muscle for hire.

1161
01:24:15,080 --> 01:24:16,229
You tell me.

1162
01:24:18,200 --> 01:24:19,918
Yeah, I remember now.

1163
01:24:20,280 --> 01:24:23,590
Meeks is a run-down ex-cop.
Same as you'll be some day.

1164
01:24:23,960 --> 01:24:25,359
That's all you'll get.

1165
01:24:26,200 --> 01:24:27,838
Keep your $20.

1166
01:24:33,240 --> 01:24:36,516
What do I get if I give you your
balls back, you wop cocksucker?

1167
01:24:40,720 --> 01:24:42,790
There was a rumor going around...

1168
01:24:43,160 --> 01:24:46,038
...that Meeks had a line
on a large supply of H.

1169
01:24:48,120 --> 01:24:48,916
And?

1170
01:24:49,720 --> 01:24:50,914
And nothing!

1171
01:24:51,280 --> 01:24:52,759
He skipped out.

1172
01:25:04,760 --> 01:25:05,795
Bullshit.

1173
01:25:06,800 --> 01:25:09,792
How would Meeks get his hands
on a large supply of heroin?

1174
01:25:10,680 --> 01:25:11,715
You're right.

1175
01:25:11,960 --> 01:25:13,678
It's probably bullshit.

1176
01:25:14,040 --> 01:25:16,349
Even if he did,
he couldn't unload it.

1177
01:25:16,760 --> 01:25:19,115
Not without drawing
all kinds of attention.

1178
01:25:19,680 --> 01:25:23,389
Maybe that's why he's under a house
in Elysian Park not smelling too good...

1179
01:25:24,920 --> 01:25:26,069
<i>...paesano.</i>

1180
01:26:16,520 --> 01:26:18,795
Maybe White's
not so dumb after all.

1181
01:26:31,640 --> 01:26:35,349
<i>We got Rita Hayworth at the morgue,
and now Veronica Lake with White.</i>

1182
01:26:35,960 --> 01:26:39,999
I think your case and my case
are connected. It's Fleur-de-Lis again.

1183
01:26:40,280 --> 01:26:41,315
Fleur-de-Lis?

1184
01:26:42,360 --> 01:26:43,759
"Whatever you desire. "

1185
01:26:44,120 --> 01:26:45,075
Porno.

1186
01:26:45,560 --> 01:26:48,120
High-class whores
cut to look like movie stars.

1187
01:26:48,480 --> 01:26:51,756
Who knows what else? Reynolds,
the kid that got killed, was involved.

1188
01:26:52,120 --> 01:26:53,519
So is Pierce Patchett.

1189
01:26:53,880 --> 01:26:54,995
The millionaire?

1190
01:26:55,640 --> 01:26:57,437
I think we should talk to him.

1191
01:26:58,320 --> 01:27:00,117
First I want to brace Stompanato.

1192
01:27:15,840 --> 01:27:18,070
Want an autograph?
Write to MGM.

1193
01:27:19,040 --> 01:27:22,032
Since when do two-bit hoods
and hookers give out autographs?

1194
01:27:22,560 --> 01:27:23,515
What?

1195
01:27:23,760 --> 01:27:24,954
LAPD. Sit down.

1196
01:27:25,200 --> 01:27:27,236
Who the hell do you think you are?

1197
01:27:27,480 --> 01:27:28,799
Take a walk, honey.

1198
01:27:29,240 --> 01:27:32,198
- You're making a large mistake.
- Get away from our table.

1199
01:27:32,560 --> 01:27:33,436
Shut up.

1200
01:27:35,000 --> 01:27:37,070
A hooker cut to look like Lana Turner
is still a hooker.

1201
01:27:38,200 --> 01:27:40,509
- She just looks like Lana Turner.
- She is Lana Turner.

1202
01:27:42,040 --> 01:27:43,712
She is Lana Turner.

1203
01:27:52,640 --> 01:27:54,232
How was I supposed to know?

1204
01:28:09,880 --> 01:28:13,395
I believe the Nite Owl's
your area of expertise, Mr. Exley.

1205
01:28:13,800 --> 01:28:16,155
I saw you on television
getting your medal.

1206
01:28:17,760 --> 01:28:18,829
And you're...

1207
01:28:19,320 --> 01:28:22,915
...that other Hollywood
celebrity policeman, aren't you?

1208
01:28:23,960 --> 01:28:27,635
The Veronica Lake look-alike works
for you. She's one of your whores.

1209
01:28:29,040 --> 01:28:32,077
- A vulgar term.
- Why's she seeing Bud White?

1210
01:28:32,440 --> 01:28:35,796
Why do men and women
usually see each other?

1211
01:28:38,720 --> 01:28:41,109
Let's try this on for size:
Fleur-de-Lis.

1212
01:28:41,720 --> 01:28:43,358
"Whatever you desire. "

1213
01:28:44,080 --> 01:28:45,433
An actor named...

1214
01:28:46,000 --> 01:28:46,876
...Matt Reynolds.

1215
01:28:48,600 --> 01:28:49,476
Nothing?

1216
01:28:52,560 --> 01:28:54,198
We want some answers.

1217
01:28:56,920 --> 01:28:58,592
We all want something.

1218
01:29:00,920 --> 01:29:02,797
The guy's as cool as they come.

1219
01:29:05,240 --> 01:29:07,834
<i>Lieutenant Exley,
come in, please. Over.</i>

1220
01:29:09,040 --> 01:29:09,790
Exley.

1221
01:29:10,040 --> 01:29:12,793
<i>The coroner wants to talk to you.
He says he has your I.D.</i>

1222
01:29:13,440 --> 01:29:16,113
Tell him Sergeant Vincennes
is coming in to talk to him.

1223
01:29:16,480 --> 01:29:18,471
- I'll drop you at your car.
- Where are you going?

1224
01:29:18,840 --> 01:29:19,989
Lynn Bracken's.

1225
01:29:20,440 --> 01:29:24,752
To find out why Patchett has her seeing
Bud White. See you at the Frolic Room.

1226
01:29:25,560 --> 01:29:28,632
Oh, great. You get the girl.
I get the coroner.

1227
01:29:38,360 --> 01:29:41,113
Hush-Hush, off the record
and on the q. t.

1228
01:29:44,760 --> 01:29:47,228
I was just coming to see you.
Got that I.D.?

1229
01:29:47,480 --> 01:29:51,678
Thank God for dental records.
Stiff used to be a cop. Leland Meeks.

1230
01:29:51,920 --> 01:29:52,796
Buzz Meeks?

1231
01:29:53,040 --> 01:29:54,314
- You knew him?
- Of him.

1232
01:29:54,560 --> 01:29:58,075
He was around when I joined the force.
Bad rep. Thanks.

1233
01:29:58,680 --> 01:29:59,874
"Just the facts. "

1234
01:30:00,120 --> 01:30:01,712
"Just the facts. "

1235
01:30:05,080 --> 01:30:05,956
Anything else?

1236
01:30:06,320 --> 01:30:10,029
Leland Meeks worked Vice '39-'41.
I need to see his arrest records.

1237
01:30:16,960 --> 01:30:17,790
Miss Bracken...

1238
01:30:18,160 --> 01:30:19,309
...I'm Lieutenant Exley.

1239
01:30:19,680 --> 01:30:20,635
I know.

1240
01:30:21,080 --> 01:30:23,036
Bud told me all about you.

1241
01:30:23,480 --> 01:30:24,515
