- Taking over Mickey Cohen's rackets.

1487
01:49:36,640 --> 01:49:40,394
Because of those pictures
I couldn't prosecute them!

1488
01:49:40,760 --> 01:49:42,034
Oh, Jesus!

1489
01:49:42,280 --> 01:49:43,156
Help me up!

1490
01:49:51,960 --> 01:49:53,996
Is that how you ran
the good-cop bad-cop?

1491
01:49:56,480 --> 01:49:57,595
Patchett?

1492
01:50:31,600 --> 01:50:34,114
Looks like his bodyguard
had a conflict of interest.

1493
01:50:40,280 --> 01:50:41,599
Suicide note.

1494
01:50:41,840 --> 01:50:46,038
Says he killed Jack because Jack had
figured out his pornography scam.

1495
01:50:46,280 --> 01:50:48,316
Slicing himself open wasn't his idea.

1496
01:50:49,720 --> 01:50:51,073
2 of his fingers are broken.

1497
01:50:51,320 --> 01:50:52,196
They held him there.

1498
01:50:54,360 --> 01:50:55,236
Or drugged him.

1499
01:50:58,560 --> 01:51:00,232
Dudley's tying up his loose ends.

1500
01:51:01,080 --> 01:51:02,308
Patchett's dead.

1501
01:51:02,560 --> 01:51:04,118
He sent you after me.

1502
01:51:05,720 --> 01:51:06,869
Lynn.

1503
01:51:07,960 --> 01:51:09,075
West Hollywood Sheriff.

1504
01:51:09,320 --> 01:51:12,039
- They're closer than we are.
- I'll get the car. Keys!

1505
01:51:19,240 --> 01:51:21,708
We took her to the station
for safekeeping.

1506
01:51:22,720 --> 01:51:26,076
Hold her as Joan Smith.
And no one sees her unless I okay it.

1507
01:51:26,840 --> 01:51:28,478
Someone worked her over.

1508
01:51:28,720 --> 01:51:30,278
She wouldn't say who.

1509
01:51:35,240 --> 01:51:36,798
See you, Exley.

1510
01:51:39,880 --> 01:51:41,313
We should talk to Lynn.

1511
01:51:42,280 --> 01:51:43,429
You do it.

1512
01:51:44,080 --> 01:51:45,149
What will you do?

1513
01:51:48,280 --> 01:51:50,111
I'm going to talk to Sid Hudgens.

1514
01:51:50,840 --> 01:51:53,354
Compliment him on his
performance at the Victory Motel.

1515
01:51:53,600 --> 01:51:55,670
Remember, Bud, we need evidence.

1516
01:51:56,840 --> 01:51:58,239
I'll get the evidence.

1517
01:52:10,280 --> 01:52:11,235
Are you okay?

1518
01:52:13,880 --> 01:52:14,835
You okay?

1519
01:52:25,080 --> 01:52:26,957
Bud hates himself for what he did.

1520
01:52:28,200 --> 01:52:30,111
I know how he feels.

1521
01:52:32,360 --> 01:52:35,079
I need to know what you
can give me on Dudley Smith.

1522
01:52:37,080 --> 01:52:39,389
He's a police captain
in business with Patchett.

1523
01:52:40,040 --> 01:52:41,519
I've never heard of him.

1524
01:52:45,560 --> 01:52:47,073
Do you have a place to stay?

1525
01:52:48,760 --> 01:52:50,193
I'll be okay.

1526
01:52:56,560 --> 01:52:58,790
Nobody goes in without official I.D.

1527
01:53:03,320 --> 01:53:04,912
It's okay. Let him through.

1528
01:53:08,360 --> 01:53:09,679
What happened?

1529
01:53:10,200 --> 01:53:13,078
Someone beat him to death,
and stole a bunch of files.

1530
01:53:13,320 --> 01:53:15,231
Must have dug up garbage
on the wrong guy.

1531
01:53:15,640 --> 01:53:17,517
We got it narrowed down
to 1000 suspects.

1532
01:53:18,760 --> 01:53:19,988
Sergeant White...

1533
01:53:20,920 --> 01:53:22,478
...dispatch got a call for you.

1534
01:53:22,720 --> 01:53:25,632
Lieutenant Exley wants you
to meet him at the Victory Motel.

1535
01:53:58,200 --> 01:53:59,713
You wanted to meet here?

1536
01:54:01,720 --> 01:54:04,632
- You called it. I thought Hudgens was...
- Hudgens is dead.

1537
01:54:15,600 --> 01:54:17,079
Let's get out of here.

1538
01:54:24,200 --> 01:54:25,519
It's too late.

1539
01:55:13,000 --> 01:55:14,991
You figured it was a set-up
but came anyway?

1540
01:55:15,240 --> 01:55:17,151
A lot of bad stuff happened here.

1541
01:55:17,680 --> 01:55:19,796
It's as good a place as any
for it to end.

1542
01:55:29,680 --> 01:55:30,669
Clip.

1543
01:55:35,600 --> 01:55:38,194
All I ever wanted
was to measure up to my father.

1544
01:55:39,240 --> 01:55:40,116
Now's your chance.

1545
01:55:42,760 --> 01:55:44,512
He died in the line of duty, didn't he?

1546
01:57:39,280 --> 01:57:40,429
Goddamn it!

1547
01:58:38,120 --> 01:58:38,791
You okay?

1548
01:58:39,680 --> 01:58:40,829
Yeah.

1549
01:58:58,600 --> 01:59:00,511
Come on. Easy.

1550
01:59:07,000 --> 01:59:07,830
Move!

1551
01:59:29,680 --> 01:59:31,033
Rollo Tomasi.

1552
01:59:34,360 --> 01:59:35,679
Who is he?

1553
01:59:36,480 --> 01:59:37,515
You are.

1554
01:59:39,720 --> 01:59:41,472
You're the guy who gets away with it.

1555
01:59:45,440 --> 01:59:46,475
Jack knew it.

1556
01:59:46,720 --> 01:59:47,948
And so do I.

1557
02:00:12,640 --> 02:00:14,278
Are you going to shoot me...

1558
02:00:15,520 --> 02:00:16,509
...or arrest me?

1559
02:00:22,640 --> 02:00:23,834
Good lad.

1560
02:00:24,640 --> 02:00:26,471
Always the politician.

1561
02:00:27,080 --> 02:00:28,832
Let me do the talking.

1562
02:00:29,440 --> 02:00:32,352
After I'm done, they'll make you
Chief of Detectives.

1563
02:00:59,080 --> 02:01:00,718
Hold up your badge...

1564
02:01:01,000 --> 02:01:02,831
...so they'll know you're a policeman.

1565
02:01:51,320 --> 02:01:54,039
<i>You think you can talk
your way out of this, Lieutenant?</i>

1566
02:01:56,560 --> 02:01:57,675
No...

1567
02:01:57,920 --> 02:01:59,433
...but I can tell the truth.

1568
02:02:00,440 --> 02:02:02,192
During our investigation...

1569
02:02:03,280 --> 02:02:06,238
...of events surrounding
the Nite Owl case...

1570
02:02:07,280 --> 02:02:10,556
...Jack Vincennes, Bud White
and I learned the following:

1571
02:02:11,280 --> 02:02:13,635
Your golden boy's
throwing his whole life away.

1572
02:02:13,880 --> 02:02:15,313
The 3 Nite Owl suspects...

1573
02:02:16,240 --> 02:02:18,595
...while guilty of
kidnapping and rape...

1574
02:02:19,360 --> 02:02:22,238
...were innocent of the
multiple homicides at the Nite Owl.

1575
02:02:23,560 --> 02:02:25,391
The gunmen were most likely...

1576
02:02:25,640 --> 02:02:30,191
...Los Angeles police officers
Michael Breuning and William Carlisle...

1577
02:02:30,440 --> 02:02:31,839
...and a third man...

1578
02:02:32,520 --> 02:02:35,990
...who may or may not have been
Captain Dudley Smith.

1579
02:02:37,040 --> 02:02:38,439
The objective:

1580
02:02:39,360 --> 02:02:41,874
The elimination of
another police officer...

1581
02:02:42,120 --> 02:02:43,838
...Richard Stensland...

1582
02:02:44,720 --> 02:02:49,475
...who, along with former LAPD officer
Leland "Buzz" Meeks...

1583
02:02:50,520 --> 02:02:54,069
...also committed multiple homicides
on behalf of Captain Smith...

1584
02:02:54,720 --> 02:02:56,233
...and then betrayed him...

1585
02:02:56,520 --> 02:02:58,636
...over 25 pounds of heroin...

1586
02:02:59,720 --> 02:03:01,472
...the retrieval of which...

1587
02:03:01,760 --> 02:03:04,672
...was the ultimate motivation
behind the Nite Owl killings.

1588
02:03:07,760 --> 02:03:10,877
Beginning with the incarceration
of Mickey Cohen...

1589
02:03:11,280 --> 02:03:15,990
...Capt. Smith has been assuming control
of organized crime in Los Angeles.

1590
02:03:17,800 --> 02:03:21,349
This includes the assassinations
of Mickey Cohen lieutenants...

1591
02:03:21,920 --> 02:03:24,957
...the systematic blackmail
of city officials...

1592
02:03:26,520 --> 02:03:30,877
...and the murders of Susan Lefferts,
Pierce Patchett, Sid Hudgens...

1593
02:03:32,240 --> 02:03:34,231
...and Sergeant Jack Vincennes.

1594
02:03:37,360 --> 02:03:40,079
Captain Smith admitted as much to me...

1595
02:03:40,680 --> 02:03:42,511
...before I shot him...

1596
02:03:42,880 --> 02:03:44,598
...at the Victory Motel.

1597
02:03:46,720 --> 02:03:47,789
That's it.

1598
02:03:52,520 --> 02:03:54,431
The press will have a field day.

1599
02:03:56,000 --> 02:03:57,353
Christ!

1600
02:03:57,600 --> 02:03:59,795
Itll stain the Department for years.

1601
02:04:00,040 --> 02:04:00,870
Decades.

1602
02:04:02,160 --> 02:04:04,628
If we can get the kid to play ball...

1603
02:04:05,640 --> 02:04:07,358
...who's to say what happened?

1604
02:04:08,440 --> 02:04:10,795
Maybe Dudley Smith died a hero.

1605
02:04:11,040 --> 02:04:13,508
- Good idea.
- If we get the press to play.

1606
02:04:21,040 --> 02:04:23,634
<i>Want to tell me what
you're smiling about?</i>

1607
02:04:28,880 --> 02:04:30,074
A hero.

1608
02:04:30,680 --> 02:04:32,272
How'd he know what we said?

1609
02:04:32,520 --> 02:04:34,078
He couldn't have heard us.

1610
02:04:37,760 --> 02:04:39,557
In this situation...

1611
02:04:39,920 --> 02:04:41,751
...you'll need more than one.

1612
02:04:48,440 --> 02:04:53,116
<i>It is my pleasure to present this award
to Detective Lieutenant Edmund Exley...</i>

1613
02:04:53,720 --> 02:04:55,676
<i>...two-time Medal of Valor recipient.</i>

1614
02:05:05,480 --> 02:05:09,268
Next year the LAPD
will move into its new facility.

1615
02:05:09,640 --> 02:05:11,232
With leaders like Edmund Exley...

1616
02:05:11,480 --> 02:05:14,438
...the image of fat cops stealing apples
will be left behind...

1617
02:05:14,680 --> 02:05:18,389
...and Los Angeles will finally
have the police force it deserves.

1618
02:05:31,760 --> 02:05:33,751
You just couldn't resist.

1619
02:05:34,040 --> 02:05:36,474
They're using me.
So for a while, I'm using them.

1620
02:05:38,440 --> 02:05:39,475
Come on.

1621
02:06:12,960 --> 02:06:14,188
Thanks for the push.

1622
02:06:35,120 --> 02:06:37,031
Congratulations, Lieutenant Exley.

1623
02:06:40,240 --> 02:06:42,231
Some men get the world...

1624
02:06:42,720 --> 02:06:46,156
...others get ex-hookers
and a trip to Arizona.

